caption: Excellent coffee, great service, and a pretty relaxed atmosphere. Definitely a good spot for hanging out or being productive.

Very very good taste of coffee, Guatemala coffee beans, delicatessen, aroma. Top 5 of the best coffee in Huntsville. Very friendly, good service, great environment, well decorated, clean, park in the street, orders to go.

Holy Coffee-moly. Honest Coffee is such a treat to have in Huntsville. My favorite coffee is a Latte - I have tried them all across HSV - and Honest reigns in supreme. I like to describe the taste as "whole" (if that makes sense). Just every sip is this big balanced wonderful experience.  *AND* they have GREAT food! I love their paninis and yummy fruit. I wish I lived right next door to them - I would happily buy from them daily.

Great atmosphere, sitting is limited, they only serve piper and leaf teas. So if your looking for Earl grey or chi this is not the place. Street parking is limited but there is garage with in short walking distance. The breakfast is half bad and ready in a reasonable amount of time. Staff is nice too!

I love the coffee, the allergy-friendly food, the location, and the atmosphere of this place. But my favorite thing about Honest, besides their commitment to community support during the pandemic, is that the staff never make me feel awkward when I ask for help running my card and adding a tip. This is a big deal because I am blind. Touch-screens and card-readers are difficult for me to manage, and a lot of people, when confronted with my inability to perform this simple task, become flustered. But the staff at Honest are always friendly, attentive, and casual about their assistance, making me feel like helping me isn't a sudden burden, but a regular part of their job description. It makes me feel very welcome, and right at home.

Sitting here at a table at HCR right now.  The shop is buzzing with chatter from all kinds of people. Looking around I see college girls doing their bible study, a pair of mid 20s ladies discussing their vegan diet, some business men going over charts and stats and discussing work, and that's all before 0900.  This is the second time I've come to this coffee shop during the weekday and have found the exact same thing.  Walking into HCR you right away get a very hipster vibe.  The interior is welcoming with a white, black and wood look.  The baristas are patient and kind as you approach the bar to order, walking you through the menu and explaining their loyalty points.  The menu is inspiring without being complicated and intimidating.  The first time I came, I just ordered a Cuban half sweet.  Very good!  This time I ordered the Smoked Salmon Bagel, Daybreak Bagel, a Mocha, and and Iced latte.  The latte is good, I'm not a coffee or espresso expert, yet but I really enjoyed the flavor.  Its not a typical Starbucks taste, it has a more unique flavor.  To sum up, the service, atmosphere and the menu items is what will be bringing me back again and again.
